Creates grails project with predefined template (file structure, dependencies, scripts etc) created by the Organisation

Usage : grails-create-app grailsVersion appName
Example: grails-create-app 2.3.6 helloApp

Creaating Template for Grails 2.x 
__________________

1. Change Grails version to 2.x. Eg. gvm use grails 2.3.7
2. grails create-app template-2-3-7 # prefix "tempalte-" grails version with . replaced by -
3. Edit template-2-3-7/grails-app/conf/Config.groovy
 Uncomment these to enable reading of external config file. External Config file will be copied to grails-app/conf dir which contains database realted configurations and default pacakage for artifacts. This file is added to .gitignore list so that your credetials are not pushed to git.

grails.config.locations = [ "classpath:${appName}-config.properties",
                             "classpath:${appName}-config.groovy",
                             "file:${userHome}/.grails/${appName}-config.properties",
                             "file:${userHome}/.grails/${appName}-config.groovy"]

4. Edit template-2-3-7/grails-app/conf/Datasource.groovy Change driverClass like this:
	driverClassName = 'com.mysql.jdbc.Driver'
 Other details lilke username, password, database url etc are configured in external config file.

 5. Edit template-2-3-7/grails-app/conf/BuildConfig.groovy and uncommennt mysql jar dependency.
